        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tui): respect queue mode in sendMessage busy guard",
        "body": "Fixes #90012\n\n## Summary\n\nThe TUI `sendMessage()` hardcodes a busy check that blocks new messages when the agent is running, completely ignoring the `/queue` mode setting configured on the Gateway. This makes `followup`, `collect`, and `interrupt` modes unusable from the TUI because messages are rejected at the client layer before reaching the Gateway's queue system.\n\nTwo additional gaps existed:\n1. The typed-submit gate (`canSubmitTuiChatMessage`) in `createEditorSubmitHandler` still blocked all gateway-mode sends during active runs, regardless of queue mode, so typed messages never reached the queue-aware `sendMessage` guard.\n2. The session row only exposed `entry?.queueMode` instead of the effective/resolved queue mode (session override > per-channel config > global config > default steer), so sessions relying on config-level defaults showed undefined and the TUI defaulted them to steer.\n\n## Changes\n\n**Gateway session row** (`session-utils.types.ts`, `session-utils.ts`): Add `queueMode` to `GatewaySessionRow` and resolve it via `resolveQueueSettings` so the row exposes the effective queue mode (not just the raw entry field). This means sessions using per-channel or global config defaults now correctly surface their non-steer mode.\n\n**TUI types** (`tui-types.ts`, `tui-backend.ts`): Add `queueMode` to `SessionInfo` and the `TuiSessionList` sessions Pick so the TUI can read the session's queue mode.\n\n**TUI session propagation** (`tui-session-actions.ts`): Propagate `queueMode` from the session entry to `state.sessionInfo` during `applySessionInfo`.\n\n**TUI busy guard** (`tui-command-handlers.ts`): Gate the `activeChatRunId` and `pendingChatRunId` checks on `queueMode === \"steer\"`. When the mode is `followup`, `collect`, or `interrupt`, the message is forwarded to the Gateway for queue handling. The `pendingOptimisticUserMessage` guard remains unconditional to prevent rapid double-sends while the previous RPC is in flight.\n\n**Typed-submit gate** (`tui.ts`): Update `canSubmitTuiChatMessage` to accept and honor `queueMode`. In steer mode (default), it blocks gateway sends during active runs and when a pending chat run exists. In non-steer modes, only `pendingOptimisticUserMessage` blocks. The caller now passes `sessionInfo.queueMode` so the editor submit handler respects the queue mode. The blocked-message notification is also queue-mode-aware.\n\n**Tests**: 13 new tests total: 7 for the queue-mode-aware `canSubmitTuiChatMessage` gate (followup/collect/interrupt allow, steer blocks, pendingOptimistic still blocks, pendingChatRunId allowed in followup), 3 for effective queue mode resolution in `buildGatewaySessionRow` (entry mode, global config fallback, default steer), and the original 3 for the command-handler busy guard + session propagation.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** TUI sendMessage blocks messages with \"agent is busy\" when the agent is running, regardless of the /queue mode setting. followup, collect, and interrupt modes never reach the Gateway. Additionally, the typed-submit path through `canSubmitTuiChatMessage` blocked messages before they reached the queue-aware sendMessage guard, and session rows only exposed the raw entry queueMode instead of the resolved effective mode.\n- **Real environment tested:** macOS 15.5, Node v22.19, OpenClaw built from patched source at `/private/tmp/proof-fix-tui-queue-mode-busy-guard`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n  Step 1. Run behavioral tests for both gates and session row:\n  ```bash\n  cd /private/tmp/proof-fix-tui-queue-mode-busy-guard\n  npm install\n  node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.tui.config.ts \\\n    src/tui/tui.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts \\\n    src/tui/tui-session-actions.test.ts\n  node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts\n  ```\n\n  Step 2. Run proof script exercising production code:\n  ```bash\n  npx tsx /tmp/proof-89078.ts\n  ```\n\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n\n  All test suites pass (63 + 57 + 31 + 107 = 258 tests):\n\n  ```console\n  $ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.tui.config.ts \\\n      src/tui/tui.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts \\\n      src/tui/tui-session-actions.test.ts\n   ✓ |tui| src/tui/tui.test.ts (63 tests) 24ms\n   ✓ |tui| src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts (57 tests) 17ms\n   ✓ |tui| src/tui/tui-session-actions.test.ts (31 tests) 12ms\n   Test Files  3 passed (3)\n        Tests  151 passed (151)\n\n  $ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts\n   ✓ |gateway| src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts (107 tests)\n   Test Files  1 passed (1)\n        Tests  107 passed (107)\n  ```\n\n  Production code proof with `canSubmitTuiChatMessage` and `resolveQueueSettings`:\n\n  ```console\n  $ npx tsx /tmp/proof-89078.ts\n\n  === Fix 1: typed-submit gate respects queueMode ===\n\n    PASS  steer blocks gateway active run: false\n    PASS  explicit steer blocks gateway active run: false\n    PASS  followup allows gateway active run: true\n    PASS  collect allows gateway active run: true\n    PASS  interrupt allows gateway active run: true\n    PASS  followup blocks pendingOptimistic: false\n    PASS  followup allows pendingChatRunId: true\n\n  === Fix 2: effective queue mode resolution ===\n\n    PASS  global config collect resolves to collect: collect\n    PASS  entry interrupt overrides global collect: interrupt\n    PASS  no config defaults to steer: steer\n    PASS  per-channel discord followup resolves: followup\n\n  === Results: 11 passed, 0 failed ===\n  ```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The production `canSubmitTuiChatMessage` gate correctly allows typed messages through in non-steer queue modes (followup, collect, interrupt) while still blocking in steer mode. The `resolveQueueSettings` function correctly resolves the effective queue mode from the full config hierarchy: entry override > per-channel config > global config > default steer. Session rows now expose the resolved effective mode instead of only the raw entry field.\n- **What was not tested:** Live TUI interaction with a running agent using `/queue mode=followup` then sending a message mid-run (requires an active provider with credentials). The end-to-end flow relies on the Gateway's existing queue system which is already tested and documented.\n\n",
